confuse: LibConfuse (A configuration file parser library)
confuse:
confuse: licensed under the terms of the LGPL, and  written  in C. It  supports
confuse: sections  and  (lists of)  values (strings, integers, floats, booleans
confuse: or other sections), as  well as some  other  features (such as single/
confuse: double-quoted strings, environment  variable  expansion, functions and
confuse: nested include statements). It makes it very easy to add configuration
confuse: file capability to a program using a simple API.
confuse:
confuse: http://www.nongnu.org/confuse/
confuse:
